Miss Delilah.

64
00:07:58,994 --> 00:08:01,313
Let's behave ourselves.

65
00:08:02,835 --> 00:08:04,294
What are you boys doing in here?

66
00:08:04,375 --> 00:08:08,133
Out, out! And what are you
doing behind that bar?

67
00:08:09,744 --> 00:08:12,203
It's just for a minute.
That's 60 seconds too long.

68
00:08:12,321 --> 00:08:13,740
Maceo, take that child's place.

69
00:08:14,427 --> 00:08:17,586
You bring people their food,
Nobody's eating!

70
00:08:20,060 --> 00:08:22,917
That's cos nobody's here
but these couple of lost souls.

71
00:08:23,077 --> 00:08:27,375
Haven't had an appetite since
they gave over to the devil.

72
00:08:33,256 --> 00:08:37,654
Evening, Maceo,
you looking good tonight!

73
00:08:37,957 --> 00:08:40,336
Likewise, Miss Nadine.

74
00:08:40,652 --> 00:08:42,032
What can I do for you?

75
00:08:42,332 --> 00:08:45,091
Oh, you know what you can do for me,
sweet man.

76
00:08:47,464 --> 00:08:49,903
What would you like... to drink?

77
00:08:56,444 --> 00:08:58,203
How many is that tonight?

78
00:08:58,720 --> 00:09:00,445
Don't talk to me about that, baby.

79
00:09:00,556 --> 00:09:03,634
Not tonight. I don't want
China Doll behind that bar.

80
00:09:03,804 --> 00:09:05,294
She's got to help out.

81
00:09:05,395 --> 00:09:08,873
Not behind there she doesn't. You
know she's not supposed to get excited.

82
00:09:09,060 --> 00:09:11,069
Not much chance of that in here.

83
00:09:11,192 --> 00:09:15,431
Harvest hands all crowded in
to Toussaint's place.

84
00:09:15,651 --> 00:09:17,380
Young ones.

85
00:09:17,491 --> 00:09:19,495
You'll get some of them.

86
00:09:19,618 --> 00:09:24,176
They'll stick their noses in here, get
one little sniff of the music and go home.

87
00:09:26,021 --> 00:09:28,165
Maybe that's the wages of sin.

88
00:09:28,275 --> 00:09:30,674
Ain't no sin happening
here tonight, baby.

89
00:09:30,814 --> 00:09:33,143
And there sure as hell
ain't no wages.

90
00:09:33,280 --> 00:09:37,437
Your God wants to chastise some sinners,
he'd best go over to Toussaint's.

91
00:09:37,653 --> 00:09:40,017
Got a whole bar room
crowded with them.

92
00:09:40,156 --> 00:09:41,765
He's not my God.

93
00:09:42,184 --> 00:09:44,404
He's everybody's God.

94
00:09:48,718 --> 00:09:50,757
How did the meeting go tonight?

95
00:09:51,510 --> 00:09:54,394
Viola Underwood found the Lord.

96
00:09:55,494 --> 00:09:58,518
If she'd found Him last,
she wouldn't have come through.

97
00:09:58,745 --> 00:10:04,863
She must have lost Him again between then and now cos
she come down that aisle tonight hollering in tongues.

98
00:10:08,164 --> 00:10:10,082
The spirit didn't move you, though?

99
00:10:11,692 --> 00:10:12,891
Not yet.

100
00:10:16,395 --> 00:10:19,014
Maybe it's too late for me.

101
00:10:23,587 --> 00:10:26,685
I can't believe he's serving
Alton Stokely. That poor man.

102
00:10:27,235 --> 00:10:29,424
Toussaint cut his credit off.

103
00:10:29,555 --> 00:10:35,053
Either he gets it here, or he drinks that paint
peeler Willie Pettigrew cuts up back in his swamp.

104
00:10:35,327 --> 00:10:37,891
I'm gonna go home,
say a prayer for that man.

105
00:10:40,546 --> 00:10:42,145
Say one for me too, baby.

106
00:10:54,184 --> 00:10:56,668
Outstanding, baby. 

107
00:10:56,812 --> 00:10:59,111
Outstanding. You've still got the voice.

108
00:10:59,247 --> 00:11:02,511
You think so? - Chills down my spine
just to hear you.

109
00:11:05,313 --> 00:11:08,251
Ty, I'm gonna be
a little late Saturday.

110
00:11:08,983 --> 00:11:12,187
No need to come in
if you don't want to.

111
00:11:14,169 --> 00:11:16,568
I've made other arrangements.

112
00:11:16,805 --> 00:11:19,654
Other arrangements?

113
00:11:17,751 --> 00:11:22,028
Try something new in here.
You can't do that. Yes, he can, darling.

114
00:11:22,250 --> 00:11:27,253
This is his place,
and he can do whatever he wants.

115
00:11:27,506 --> 00:11:29,350
You'll know where to find me when you need me. 

116
00:11:39,440 --> 00:11:41,859
Put the box on now, Ty?

117
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:44,349
Yeah, put the box on.

118
00:11:44,487 --> 00:11:48,366
I'm gonna crank it up some,
see if we can draw some life in here.

119
00:11:51,620 --> 00:11:53,779
LOUD JAZZ MUSIC

120
00:12:02,255 --> 00:12:04,019
There it goes again.

121
00:12:04,132 --> 00:12:07,691
Electricity don't like that jukebox.

122
00:12:14,476 --> 00:12:16,800
Must be a short circuit
in the juke here.

123
00:12:16,937 --> 00:12:20,735
Got to get the power company No,
they turned my juice off last month.

124
00:12:20,936 --> 00:12:24,580
I don't want you sniffing
around that splice out Maceo did.

125
00:12:24,774 --> 00:12:27,215
It's nice in here.

126
00:12:27,357 --> 00:12:29,729
Kind of romantic.

127
00:12:29,868 --> 00:12:33,306
I'm gonna have to go out back,
wiggle some things around.

128
00:12:33,491 --> 00:12:36,894
Don't you wiggle nothing round
unless I'm there to see it.

129
00:12:37,078 --> 00:12:40,082
You don't worry, folks,
bar's still open.

130
00:12:47,595 --> 00:12:49,674
Evening, folks.

131
00:12:54,310 --> 00:12:57,169
Evening, Sherriff.

132
00:12:57,329 --> 00:13:00,153
Your light's gone out.

133
00:13:00,311 --> 00:13:02,200
Looks like it.

134
00:13:02,319 --> 00:13:05,398
You'll know that'll be a violation
of something or other.

135
00:13:05,567 --> 00:13:07,651
We're just about to close up here.

136
00:13:09,326 --> 00:13:11,684
Oh. Ooh, your wife been cooking?

137
00:13:11,822 --> 00:13:13,791
Not tonight.

138
00:13:13,913 --> 00:13:15,677
Went to a revival chat.

139
00:13:15,790 --> 00:13:19,114
Ah, I stood by there myself.

140
00:13:19,294 --> 00:13:22,817
Them niggers were singing up a storm.

141
00:13:23,006 --> 00:13:25,885
I just came out here
to look in on Toussaint.

142
00:13:26,046 --> 00:13:29,770
Had that shooting two nights ago.

143
00:13:29,967 --> 00:13:31,971
Lots of fighting in there.

144
00:13:32,094 --> 00:13:34,623
There is that.

145
00:13:34,769 --> 00:13:38,087
Course, me and old Toussaint,

146
00:13:38,267 --> 00:13:40,751
we got us an agreement.

147
00:13:44,070 --> 00:13:47,514
Them field hands
start sucking down that whisky,

148
00:13:47,700 --> 00:13:51,937
hopping them all up with music,
there's gonna be some razors drawn.

149
00:13:54,122 --> 00:13:56,606
Course, he only call me
if it's a fatality.

150
00:13:56,750 --> 00:14:01,508
Never been a killing here. Them
youngbloods know better than to mess...

151
00:14:01,750 --> 00:14:04,839
Than to mess with Tyrone Purvis.

152
00:14:05,009 --> 00:14:08,507
You've got quite a reputation
round here, Tyrone.

153
00:14:08,694 --> 00:14:12,158
People say you put some poor
black boy in the grave.

154
00:14:18,523 --> 00:14:20,602
Just people talking.

155
00:14:20,728 --> 00:14:23,217
Uh-huh.

156
00:14:23,361 --> 00:14:24,924
You just remember,

157
00:14:25,028 --> 00:14:27,113
this is my county, Tyrone.

158
00:14:27,240 --> 00:14:30,283
What goes on goes on cos I let it.

159
00:14:30,451 --> 00:14:33,810
Don't want nobody getting too big
for their breeches round here.

160
00:14:38,668 --> 00:14:40,867
You folks have a pleasant evening.

161
00:14:53,309 --> 00:14:54,988
Nigger ain't shit in this world.

162
00:14:56,521 --> 00:14:58,925
Speaking for yourself.

163
00:14:59,065 --> 00:15:04,142
You ain't had his club, Tyrone,
what do you think you'd be?

164
00:15:04,398 --> 00:15:06,962
You wouldn't be nothing.

165
00:15:08,658 --> 00:15:11,976
If that ain't truth,
then grits ain't grocery.

166
00:15:28,012 --> 00:15:31,256
TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS

167
00:15:31,432 --> 00:15:34,675
That's a terrible noise.

168
00:15:34,852 --> 00:15:38,490
Just the northbound Talladega.
Sounds like it always does.

169
00:15:38,684 --> 00:15:42,567
Like a soul being carried away
from this life.

170
00:15:47,698 --> 00:15:49,302
Come on in, darling,

171
00:15:49,408 --> 00:15:51,408
before you catch
your death out here.

172
00:16:24,987 --> 00:16:29,505
You're lucky the high sheriff ain't
seen you crawling out that boxcar.

173
00:16:29,737 --> 00:16:32,981
Does he come around here much?Only when he bored.

174
00:16:34,706 --> 00:16:37,305
You working on a train?Yeah, Kansas City to New Orleans.

175
00:16:37,453 --> 00:16:40,034
What did you get off here for?

176
00:16:40,183 --> 00:16:42,596
I got people here. How about you?

177
00:16:42,736 --> 00:16:45,114
Got tired of sleeping in a boxcar.

178
00:16:47,094 --> 00:16:49,693
Is there a place to stay
around here?

179
00:16:49,842 --> 00:16:51,291
Shed right over there got a cot.

180
00:16:51,390 --> 00:16:54,868
And don't mind the rats.
Not unless you've got food on you.

181
00:16:55,055 --> 00:16:58,464
I see you and a good meal have
been strangers for some time.

182
00:16:58,647 --> 00:17:03,564
Get into town tomorrow, find you need
something, tell them Shack Thomas sent you.

183
00:17:03,814 --> 00:17:08,458
They'll know who you're
talking about. Thanks.

184
00:17:13,079 --> 00:17:16,357
Name like that sounds like
a good place for a musician.

185
00:17:18,085 --> 00:17:22,083
Only night I ever been in jail
was a town called Liberty.

186
00:17:22,292 --> 00:17:24,616
The sun come up,
you'll see where you landed.

187
00:17:30,806 --> 00:17:33,404
You'd best be out that shed
by first light.

188
00:17:51,744 --> 00:17:56,102
Just a weekday night.
The chicken man or the ice man

189
00:17:56,327 --> 00:17:58,651
At least you don't owe
the electric company.

190
00:17:58,788 --> 00:18:00,513
Yeah, that's a big relief.

191
00:18:07,093 --> 00:18:08,852
You thinking about closing down?

192
00:18:18,147 --> 00:18:21,030
What do you think?The biggest act in New Orleans.

193
00:18:21,191 --> 00:18:24,390
Got him a hit on the radio.
He's playing here Saturday night.

194
00:18:24,565 --> 00:18:27,729
I'm thinking I wait till Bertha Mae
was gone and I put him up.

195
00:18:27,902 --> 00:18:29,511
Here?

196
00:18:29,617 --> 00:18:31,821
You mean like in this room here?

197
00:18:31,953 --> 00:18:33,757
You know the Tomcat Club
in Texicana?

198
00:18:33,872 --> 00:18:37,071
Big Jim Jameson's place?
It just went out of business.

199
00:18:37,245 --> 00:18:44,771
Damn. Since Sam is getting sway over

200
00:18:45,133 --> 00:18:49,131
But you ain't never had no guitar...
I'm having one now.

201
00:18:52,474 --> 00:18:56,117
You just worry about getting these
hung everywhere in the county tomorrow.

202
00:18:56,311 --> 00:19:01,789
Payday Saturday, he's gonna draw all them
cotton pickers and soldier boys in here.

203
00:19:02,063 --> 00:19:04,024
Get us back in the black.

204
00:19:04,145 --> 00:19:06,248
They're gonna take me down,

205
00:19:06,375 --> 00:19:08,468
it won't be without a fight.

206
00:19:08,595 --> 00:19:10,654
Guitar Sam at the Honeydripper!

207
00:19:10,780 --> 00:19:12,430
Mm-hm!

208
00:19:12,537 --> 00:19:15,535
Man, this joint is gonna jump!

209
00:20:08,428 --> 00:20:09,787
BELL TINKLES

210
00:20:53,934 --> 00:20:56,573
GUITAR STRUMMING

211
00:21:02,902 --> 00:21:05,261
Somebody slipped
in the railroad yard.

212
00:21:12,953 --> 00:21:15,197
You all can play that thing.

213
00:21:15,331 --> 00:21:18,490
Yeah, been doing it nearby for ever.

214
00:21:20,336 --> 00:21:22,055
What side of the tracks am I on?

215
00:21:22,166 --> 00:21:23,931
The wrong side.

216
00:21:24,044 --> 00:21:25,973
For you.

217
00:21:26,093 --> 00:21:29,136
What you doing here, then?

218
00:21:29,304 --> 00:21:32,108
Oh, white folks
look right through me.

219
00:21:32,265 --> 00:21:37,343
Besides, how much mischief is an old,
blind spook like me gonna get up to anyhow?

220
00:21:38,815 --> 00:21:41,618
Lot of people go for music
around here?

221
00:21:41,775 --> 00:21:46,253
There's a couple of places just
outside of town, at the crossroads.

222
00:21:46,483 --> 00:21:49,166
A long walk? Are you in a hurry?

223
00:21:53,037 --> 00:21:57,675
How old is that box you're playing,Second one ever made.

224
00:21:57,912 --> 00:22:01,715
The devil got the first one.
How about yours?

225
00:22:01,916 --> 00:22:04,805
Brand new. Made it myself.

226
00:22:04,966 --> 00:22:07,805
Ooh, brand new! Made it hisself!

227
00:22:07,964 --> 00:22:10,945
Hot dog! It's right.

228
00:22:11,111 --> 00:22:14,022
So, these clubs?

229
00:22:14,184 --> 00:22:16,923
Old Toussaint,
he runs the Ace of Spades.

230
00:22:17,078 --> 00:22:19,747
They don't have no live music
in there.

231
00:22:19,899 --> 00:22:23,057
Pine Top Purvis, he runs
the Honeydripper Lounge.

232
00:22:23,230 --> 00:22:25,679
He don't care nothing
about no guitar.

233
00:22:25,821 --> 00:22:29,219
He won't allow one under his roof.
That don't make sense.

234
00:22:29,402 --> 00:22:33,126
Well, when a musician
put his hand to murder,

235
00:22:33,324 --> 00:22:37,287
nine times out of ten
a drummer done it.

236
00:22:37,495 --> 00:22:40,064
But Pine Top, he a piano man.

237
00:22:40,211 --> 00:22:43,529
He killed somebody?That's the story.

238
00:22:44,632 --> 00:22:48,630
But if you meet the man, you damn
well don't be asking him about it.

239
00:22:57,939 --> 00:23:00,017
HONKING

240
00:23:14,038 --> 00:23:16,077
Ain't seen no mule in a long time!

241
00:23:17,750 --> 00:23:21,668
I knew this was Alabama,
but that's the Stone Ages, man!

242
00:23:21,874 --> 00:23:23,438
Where you from, boy?

243
00:23:23,542 --> 00:23:25,072
Memphis.

244
00:23:25,175 --> 00:23:27,499
Down on your vacation?

245
00:23:27,636 --> 00:23:30,075
Got in a piece of trouble up there
with the white folks.

246
00:23:30,217 --> 00:23:31,986
Need to bide my time for a spell.

247
00:23:32,099 --> 00:23:34,697
Biding your time
with them pills, man,

248
00:23:34,846 --> 00:23:36,415
boss man gonna fire your ass.

249
00:23:36,519 --> 00:23:39,558
Don't worry about that.
I'm a cotton-picking fool!

250
00:23:41,483 --> 00:23:43,003
You a fool all right.

251
00:23:53,704 --> 00:23:56,843
Where you from, brother bear?
Mississippi.

252
00:23:57,015 --> 00:24:00,084
Hoo! This here
is a real step-up for you!

253
00:24:00,253 --> 00:24:03,251
Folks around here have discovered
fire and whatnot!

254
00:24:06,802 --> 00:24:10,605
That trouble you in,

255
00:24:10,806 --> 00:24:13,329
have anything to do
with running your mouth?

256
00:24:13,474 --> 00:24:17,792
It had to do with somebody getting on
my nerves and I had to deal with him.

257
00:24:18,015 --> 00:24:20,237
Must have been somebody kinda puny.

258
00:24:20,370 --> 00:24:22,557
As I recall, he was about your size.

259
00:24:45,467 --> 00:24:49,025
What's this place we at?
Nearest town's Harmony.

260
00:24:49,215 --> 00:24:51,339
This is Mr Silas Tugwell's place.

261
00:24:53,099 --> 00:24:55,638
You better get to picking. Cotton ain't going nowhere.

262
00:24:55,784 --> 00:24:58,288
The more you get first thing
when the dew's still on it,

263
00:24:58,433 --> 00:25:00,077
the more it weighs
when it tip that scale.

264
00:25:03,610 --> 00:25:05,089
You live here too?

265
00:25:08,073 --> 00:25:09,713
You got my sympathies.

266
00:25:19,795 --> 00:25:22,398
Hot damn!

267
00:25:22,547 --> 00:25:24,950
What's the matter? I got a shock.

268
00:25:25,090 --> 00:25:26,850
I thought you used to work
for the power company.

269
00:25:26,963 --> 00:25:30,451
I drove the supply truck.

270
00:25:30,638 --> 00:25:34,557
Guitar Sam ain't gonna be playing
by no candlelight.

271
00:25:36,895 --> 00:25:38,219
I smell bacon.

272
00:25:38,313 --> 00:25:42,631
You must have burned your porky ass
with that electricity!

273
00:25:44,654 --> 00:25:46,373
Breakfast's ready!

274
00:25:48,115 --> 00:25:50,679
Where your mama?She already over to the mayor's.

275
00:25:50,826 --> 00:25:54,904
She told me to make sure you eat
something before you start running 'round.

276
00:25:55,117 --> 00:25:57,726
That is a sweet woman you got.

277
00:25:57,875 --> 00:26:01,353
You got one waiting for you
if you want her. Who, Nadine?

278
00:26:01,540 --> 00:26:04,983
She come in here every night
making them cow eyes at you.

279
00:26:05,169 --> 00:26:07,413
She seem like a kind
who could smother a man.

280
00:26:07,546 --> 00:26:09,036
She makes all her own clothes.

281
00:26:09,137 --> 00:26:11,136
Darlin', that's not
the kind of thing

282
00:26:11,259 --> 00:26:13,303
a man cares about from a woman.

283
00:26:13,428 --> 00:26:14,877
MUSIC BLARES

284
00:26:14,976 --> 00:26:18,015
Hey, I fixed it!You ain't done no such thing.

285
00:26:18,183 --> 00:26:20,904
It just decided to come back on.
Decided? Yeah.

286
00:26:21,058 --> 00:26:23,745
Just like it decided
to switch off last night.

287
00:26:23,897 --> 00:26:25,986
You ain't even in the conversation!

288
00:26:26,113 --> 00:26:29,831
This Nadine makes some good money,
too, sewing for people.

289
00:26:30,028 --> 00:26:31,638
That woman scares me.

290
00:26:31,745 --> 00:26:34,763
Last ol' boy to give her a tumble,

291
00:26:34,929 --> 00:26:37,877
Napier Carpenter,
she cooked for him.

292
00:26:38,041 --> 00:26:41,799
Fixed him up all kinds
of nice, new clothes...

293
00:26:41,998 --> 00:26:43,648
I don't see no problem with that!

294
00:26:43,756 --> 00:26:45,995
Come four, five months,
a man starts to...

295
00:26:47,677 --> 00:26:50,556
Sorry, China Doll,
but this is just the way it is.

296
00:26:50,717 --> 00:26:53,326
A man gots needs.

297
00:26:53,475 --> 00:26:56,998
Looks like Nadine could
take care of those, too.

298
00:26:57,187 --> 00:27:00,466
You eat chicken every morning,
noon and night for five months,

299
00:27:00,644 --> 00:27:03,728
you get a taste
for a different kind of meat.

300
00:27:05,112 --> 00:27:09,350
Maybe I shouldn't be talking
about this in front of China Doll.

301
00:27:09,570 --> 00:27:13,099
You ain't gonna say something
I haven't heard worse.

302
00:27:13,288 --> 00:27:19,524
Well, Napier goes out and has him
a pork chop or two, let's say.

303
00:27:22,463 --> 00:27:26,062
Comes back one night
from Toussaint's place,

304
00:27:26,254 --> 00:27:28,977
feeling no pain and smelling...

305
00:27:30,305 --> 00:27:33,509
.. Like pork chops,
the way a man will.

306
00:27:33,684 --> 00:27:37,887
He falls out on Nadine's couch
and commenced to snore.

307
00:27:38,105 --> 00:27:43,623
Wake up next morning, find she had taken
all his clothes off without him knowing.

308
00:27:43,898 --> 00:27:46,027
The man was dog drunk!

309
00:27:46,155 --> 00:27:48,753
Miss Nadine come back
with a skillet in her hand,

310
00:27:48,902 --> 00:27:50,232
hot grits bubbling in it.

311
00:27:50,326 --> 00:27:55,488
Says, "Baby, I got your breakfast".

312
00:27:55,748 --> 00:27:59,866
"Oh, not this morning, Nadine",
he says, sitting up.

313
00:28:00,080 --> 00:28:01,924
"Don't think I could eat a thing."

314
00:28:03,590 --> 00:28:08,867
"Well then", she says, "we can't
let this go to waste, can we?"

315
00:28:09,131 --> 00:28:13,774
and she dumped
that whole hot bubbling mess

316
00:28:14,011 --> 00:28:16,775
right in that man's lap.

317
00:28:16,931 --> 00:28:19,100
Ouch!

318
00:28:19,231 --> 00:28:26,348
Then she got busy
with that hot iron on his head.

319
00:28:26,692 --> 00:28:29,455
If screams didn't bring
the neighbours in,

320
00:28:29,611 --> 00:28:31,413
she'd have killed that man.

321
00:28:31,527 --> 00:28:33,259
You've got to admit it though,

322
00:28:33,370 --> 00:28:37,968
the woman is an artist when
it comes to that Singer machine.

323
00:28:38,204 --> 00:28:39,688
Excuse me.

324
00:28:41,420 --> 00:28:44,659
Which one of you is Mr Pine Top?

325
00:28:51,222 --> 00:28:53,222
We ain't hiring.

326
00:28:54,643 --> 00:28:56,487
I can play anything.

327
00:28:56,603 --> 00:28:58,882
I already got me a professional.

328
00:29:00,775 --> 00:29:04,253
Guitar Sam really comin'
all the way down here?

329
00:29:04,440 --> 00:29:06,203
That so surprising?

330
00:29:06,315 --> 00:29:09,444
No, no.

331
00:29:09,616 --> 00:29:13,174
Mr Shack Thomas told me... You know Shack?

332
00:29:13,364 --> 00:29:16,813
We... travelled together.

333
00:29:16,999 --> 00:29:20,398
When was the last time
you ate solid food, young man?

334
00:29:23,130 --> 00:29:27,289
Take him back and fix him something,
China Doll.

335
00:29:27,505 --> 00:29:30,628
Standing there all hungry-eyed,

336
00:29:30,800 --> 00:29:33,421
puts me off my breakfast.

337
00:29:33,570 --> 00:29:36,157
That's real kind of you.

338
00:29:53,036 --> 00:29:55,715
Must've come in
on the north-bound last night.

339
00:29:55,867 --> 00:29:58,328
Looks like he got the cooties too.

340
00:29:58,471 --> 00:30:00,898
Straw in them box cars, full of 'em.

341
00:30:01,039 --> 00:30:02,968
Never cared to travel that way.

342
00:30:03,088 --> 00:30:06,607
I was out there riding them rails
between the wars.

343
00:30:06,796 --> 00:30:08,445
Hm...

344
00:30:08,553 --> 00:30:11,771
Seen black half of the country
headin' west.

345
00:30:11,946 --> 00:30:15,095
Rode past the other half
coming back east.

346
00:30:15,268 --> 00:30:19,546
Yeah, every one of us,
scraping for the next meal.

347
00:30:21,316 --> 00:30:24,315
This is the place.
Y'all can tear things down.

348
00:30:24,481 --> 00:30:27,410
Put things up.
It's got a lot of potential.

349
00:30:27,573 --> 00:30:32,490
It looks bigger than it does from the
outside. Can I help you, gentlemen?

350
00:30:32,739 --> 00:30:36,583
I'm just showing the man who
gonna run this place what he got.

351
00:30:41,170 --> 00:30:42,889
This is my place.

352
00:30:52,224 --> 00:30:54,228
You the piano player, right?

353
00:30:54,351 --> 00:30:58,148
My name's Tyrone.
They call me Pine Top Purvis.

354
00:30:58,349 --> 00:31:01,073
Pine Top Purvis.

355
00:31:01,227 --> 00:31:02,556
You owe 200

356
00:31:02,650 --> 00:31:05,849
to Lucky Hardaway up in Little Rock.

357
00:31:06,024 --> 00:31:07,708
He gonna get his.

358
00:31:07,817 --> 00:31:10,266
Pine Top...

359
00:31:10,408 --> 00:31:13,047
You missed last month's rent.

360
00:31:13,198 --> 00:31:14,807
After this weekend.

361
00:31:14,913 --> 00:31:20,151
After this weekend, you gonna be
the same raggedy arse piano player

362
00:31:20,414 --> 00:31:22,663
who can't pay off his debts.

363
00:31:22,797 --> 00:31:26,956
Mr Simmons here,
he's gonna be the new proprietor.

364
00:31:27,172 --> 00:31:28,701
Lucky give me two weeks.

365
00:31:28,803 --> 00:31:32,080
Lucky got a better offer. He can't do that.

366
00:31:34,559 --> 00:31:36,678
You don't think so?

367
00:31:38,563 --> 00:31:42,326
Whoa, now!

368
00:31:42,525 --> 00:31:45,404
What if we got our payments
for him Monday?

369
00:31:45,565 --> 00:31:48,329
Saturday night. We can do that.

370
00:31:50,033 --> 00:31:52,352
Not just no taste.

371
00:31:52,489 --> 00:31:54,738
The whole 200.

372
00:31:54,871 --> 00:32:00,709
And I'll throw in a 25 cent tip
for his messenger boy.

373
00:32:00,998 --> 00:32:03,099
In the meantime,

374
00:32:03,227 --> 00:32:05,259
we're not open yet.

375
00:32:05,383 --> 00:32:07,262
That means y'all trespassing.

376
00:32:12,514 --> 00:32:14,793
See enough, Mr Simmons?

377
00:32:14,928 --> 00:32:17,092
I believe I have.

378
00:32:20,440 --> 00:32:23,839
Somebody could do something
with this place.

379
00:32:25,695 --> 00:32:27,654
Wouldn't take a whole lot of work.

380
00:32:33,120 --> 00:32:36,803
We cleared over 200 that oneA couple of years back.

381
00:32:36,999 --> 00:32:40,238
And we didn't have no Luther on
the guitar with the playing meter.

382
00:32:40,414 --> 00:32:43,623
They say it draws them like flies. That's what they say.

383
00:32:43,798 --> 00:32:47,395
They say first thing he does
is go to the man that owns a joint,

384
00:32:47,587 --> 00:32:50,391
sticks out his hand and
watch that cash money put in it.

385
00:32:50,549 --> 00:32:52,198
I already sent 50 to his manager.

386
00:32:52,306 --> 00:32:54,870
How much you paying him all out?Another hundred.

387
00:32:55,017 --> 00:32:59,455
We need to clear 300! What I figure
is if we charge folks 2 to get in,

388
00:32:59,684 --> 00:33:01,014
then the liquor...

389
00:33:01,108 --> 00:33:04,066
What I'm saying is
'less he see that green up front,

390
00:33:04,230 --> 00:33:06,075
the man won't get off the train!

391
00:33:06,191 --> 00:33:08,155
HORN HONKS

392
00:33:09,241 --> 00:33:10,881
What's that now?

393
00:33:17,792 --> 00:33:19,710
About time you fellas run by!

394
00:33:19,829 --> 00:33:21,713
We're just about dry here!

395
00:33:21,831 --> 00:33:23,453
Boss in?

396
00:33:23,560 --> 00:33:25,112
Tyrone?

397
00:33:25,215 --> 00:33:27,174
Whisky wagon come by.

398
00:33:31,055 --> 00:33:32,539
Y'all a day late!

399
00:33:32,640 --> 00:33:35,564
The old man Toussaint
gonna chew me out!

400
00:33:35,727 --> 00:33:39,485
Toussaint went over
to another supplier upstate.

401
00:33:39,684 --> 00:33:40,694
We just got you,

402
00:33:40,774 --> 00:33:44,692
then we're over to the army base
to service the officers' club.

403
00:33:44,898 --> 00:33:46,862
That's 56.

404
00:33:48,698 --> 00:33:50,978
My credit no good anymore?

405
00:33:55,331 --> 00:33:57,215
Whoa, whoa. What's your hurry?

406
00:33:57,333 --> 00:34:00,331
Nobody in their right mind
sell liquor on credit,

407
00:34:00,497 --> 00:34:03,341
especially not to no
dark town road house.

408
00:34:03,500 --> 00:34:05,341
Listen, I got a special case, see.

409
00:34:05,458 --> 00:34:07,230
We've got the harvest coming up.

410
00:34:07,343 --> 00:34:11,261
Soldiers at the base gonna be let
off on leave Saturday night.

411
00:34:11,467 --> 00:34:15,351
Ain't enough hooch in this truck
to satisfy what we gonna sell!

412
00:34:15,555 --> 00:34:19,758
You pay as you go, that's business.

413
00:34:19,976 --> 00:34:23,065
Look, you come back Monday,

414
00:34:23,235 --> 00:34:28,952
get paid and take back
every damn drop that I don't sell.

415
00:34:29,236 --> 00:34:33,799
OK, we got Guitar Sam
lined up here...

416
00:34:36,498 --> 00:34:42,136
What... What if I throw in 5
up front for you fellas?

417
00:34:42,416 --> 00:34:44,537
ENGINE STARTS

418
00:34:44,665 --> 00:34:46,668
Hey! Wait.

419
00:34:46,791 --> 00:34:48,759
Come on, man!

420
00:34:52,223 --> 00:34:54,022
Everybody gives credit!

421
00:34:54,136 --> 00:34:55,900
It's the American way!

422
00:35:06,238 --> 00:35:10,436
Maybe we could buy some Bushead
from Willie Pettigrew.

423
00:35:10,654 --> 00:35:13,537
With that sheriff sniffing
'round me every night,

424
00:35:13,698 --> 00:35:15,902
lay my black ass in jail for good.

425
00:35:16,033 --> 00:35:17,723
Then what we gonna do?

426
00:35:17,833 --> 00:35:21,591
# Move it on over,
move it on over... #

427
00:35:27,760 --> 00:35:30,398
Got a load of liquor
for a Mr Lucien Toussaint.

428
00:35:30,549 --> 00:35:33,198
That would be me.

429
00:35:33,349 --> 00:35:35,313
I trust he got my cheque all right.

430
00:35:35,434 --> 00:35:37,479
Don't suppose I'd be here
if they didn't.

431
00:35:37,604 --> 00:35:40,842
Pull round to the back,
we'll help you unload.

432
00:35:53,870 --> 00:35:57,748
This better be some Saturday night.

433
00:35:59,501 --> 00:36:02,140
Arkansas. How about you?

434
00:36:03,255 --> 00:36:06,454
We come here just after mama
met my stepdaddy.

435
00:36:06,629 --> 00:36:09,793
Not much going on
in a little town like this.

436
00:36:11,514 --> 00:36:15,432
They started up the training base
again. Is that right?

437
00:36:20,231 --> 00:36:21,911
You been in the army?

438
00:36:22,020 --> 00:36:23,629
Uh-huh.

439
00:36:23,735 --> 00:36:25,813
You shoot people?

440
00:36:25,940 --> 00:36:27,984
Fixed radios.

441
00:36:33,077 --> 00:36:35,756
They say this new war
gonna be a short one.

442
00:36:35,909 --> 00:36:39,513
Might be, might not.

443
00:36:41,170 --> 00:36:42,329
I was in Japan.

444
00:36:42,415 --> 00:36:44,704
Yeah?

445
00:36:44,840 --> 00:36:47,120
What's the people like there?

446
00:36:47,255 --> 00:36:49,116
Small. Yeah?

447
00:36:49,233 --> 00:36:50,746
About...

448
00:36:50,848 --> 00:36:52,291
that high.

449
00:36:52,389 --> 00:36:54,309
Speak Japanese.

450
00:36:59,981 --> 00:37:01,980
You been to California?

451
00:37:02,103 --> 00:37:04,152
Los Angeles.

452
00:37:04,277 --> 00:37:08,160
Where they make the movies?
You go to movies? I've been once.

453
00:37:08,364 --> 00:37:12,802
A fine looking girl like you ought
to have been all kinds of places.

454
00:37:13,031 --> 00:37:15,520
I'm going to 'em, I just...

455
00:37:15,664 --> 00:37:17,543
First I'm going to beauty school.

456
00:37:17,660 --> 00:37:19,921
When mama saves up the money.

457
00:37:20,056 --> 00:37:22,283
Then I'll have a portable skill.

458
00:37:22,415 --> 00:37:24,424
Like playing music?

459
00:37:24,548 --> 00:37:27,027
My stepdaddy says that ain't a skill.

460
00:37:27,170 --> 00:37:28,495
It's an affliction.

461
00:37:31,640 --> 00:37:33,364
Come on, China Doll.

462
00:37:33,475 --> 00:37:36,434
Business in town.
You gonna help wi' it.

463
00:37:38,062 --> 00:37:42,060
And you young man, you wanna point
yourself west down that highway

464
00:37:42,269 --> 00:37:46,073
about three miles
to the people working in the field.

465
00:37:46,274 --> 00:37:48,563
It's harvest time.

466
00:37:48,698 --> 00:37:52,296
If you can stoop and pull,
they got a job for you.

467
00:37:52,488 --> 00:37:54,372
Wash up the dishes before you go.

468
00:38:03,047 --> 00:38:05,726
What I need is for you
to go get friendly with Luther,

469
00:38:05,878 --> 00:38:06,967
then I just happen in.

470
00:38:07,051 --> 00:38:08,816
We can't just ask Mr Skinner?

471
00:38:08,928 --> 00:38:11,606
Mr Skinner don't want nothing
from coloured folk,

472
00:38:11,759 --> 00:38:14,003
but they buy his goods
and shine his shoes.

473
00:38:14,136 --> 00:38:16,460
You go on ahead now.

474
00:38:31,076 --> 00:38:33,515
GUITAR STRUMMING

475
00:38:38,208 --> 00:38:40,427
# It was early

476
00:38:40,560 --> 00:38:42,744
# Friday evening

477
00:38:44,089 --> 00:38:47,768
# And the hound began to bark

478
00:38:49,011 --> 00:38:52,249
# Staggolee and Billy Lyons

479
00:38:52,425 --> 00:38:55,629
# Squabbling in the dark

480
00:38:57,853 --> 00:39:01,171
# Staggolee told Billy Lyons

481
00:39:02,358 --> 00:39:05,437
# "What do you think about that?

482
00:39:08,948 --> 00:39:11,792
# "First you take all my money

483
00:39:11,951 --> 00:39:15,790
# "Then you spits
in my Stetson hat"... #

484
00:39:19,042 --> 00:39:20,922
I hate that damn song.

485
00:39:23,089 --> 00:39:25,288
How you been keeping, Tyrone?

486
00:39:25,419 --> 00:39:27,348
Well, just...

487
00:39:27,468 --> 00:39:29,231
trying to hold it together.

488
00:39:29,344 --> 00:39:32,783
You've got your beautiful young
daughter with you this morning.

489
00:39:32,968 --> 00:39:34,372
Don't you be studying her.

490
00:39:37,019 --> 00:39:40,698
I heard tell you gonna put
on a guitar man out at your place.

491
00:39:40,893 --> 00:39:42,654
Where you hear that?

492
00:39:42,767 --> 00:39:44,494
Oh... The breeze.

493
00:39:46,237 --> 00:39:49,636
Well, this time the breeze know
what it's blowing about.

494
00:39:51,367 --> 00:39:53,931
You'd better be careful, Tyrone.

495
00:39:54,079 --> 00:39:57,238
Cos you know what them
guitar players are like.

496
00:39:58,959 --> 00:40:00,479
You be careful yourself.

497
00:40:02,338 --> 00:40:05,615
# He shot him in the shoulder

498
00:40:07,509 --> 00:40:10,508
# Three times in the side

499
00:40:12,598 --> 00:40:14,797
# That's the last time he shot him

500
00:40:16,310 --> 00:40:18,789
# Poor Billy up and died

501
