and the bill is passed due.

504
00:40:30,575 --> 00:40:33,934
You know Mr Roosevelt would've
done it already, only he died.

505
00:40:34,115 --> 00:40:37,883
They don't listen to Miss Eleanor
no more but Mr Truman,

506
00:40:38,083 --> 00:40:41,761
he's starting a band, especially now
that we got this war heated up.

507
00:40:41,956 --> 00:40:43,765
Brother Randolph says...

508
00:40:43,880 --> 00:40:48,443
Here it comes! The gospel
according to Randolph

509
00:40:48,677 --> 00:40:52,995
Tyrone! How you doing?
Oh, got my nose above the waterline.

510
00:40:53,218 --> 00:40:57,502
Here's my baby. What's up, Ty?How your mama doing, China Doll?

511
00:40:57,723 --> 00:40:59,652
She doing fine, Uncle Shack.

512
00:40:59,772 --> 00:41:02,735
I'm just telling the boys here
about how Brother Randolph

513
00:41:02,900 --> 00:41:06,259
pushing this deal how boys are gonna
be a full part of the service.

514
00:41:06,441 --> 00:41:07,810
I carried a rifle in the Great War.

515
00:41:07,905 --> 00:41:10,024
Boys get in the middle
of this Korea mess,

516
00:41:10,152 --> 00:41:12,202
they ain't gonna thank you
for your efforts.

517
00:41:12,328 --> 00:41:15,886
If we want our full due in this
country, we've got to go ho ho!

518
00:41:16,076 --> 00:41:19,359
Black folk shooting yellow folk
to keep white folks happy?

519
00:41:19,537 --> 00:41:22,106
We need to move on
from that kind of thinking.

520
00:41:22,254 --> 00:41:26,532
Move right on, Shack. Then come back
and tell the rest of us how it is.

521
00:41:26,753 --> 00:41:28,157
LAUGHTER

522
00:41:30,345 --> 00:41:32,784
That's a hard headed man.

523
00:41:34,475 --> 00:41:37,718
I'd have to ask Mr Skinner.
Of course you would.

524
00:41:37,895 --> 00:41:41,294
While you're at it, remind him how one
of the reasons coloured folks come here

525
00:41:41,477 --> 00:41:43,881
is to get the low-down
on what's happening.

526
00:41:44,022 --> 00:41:47,870
China doll! You gonna let us put

527
00:41:48,072 --> 00:41:50,676
I don't think that will be
any problem at all.

528
00:41:50,825 --> 00:41:54,383
That's awful nice of you, Luther. You're looking special today.

529
00:41:54,574 --> 00:41:56,623
That's sweet of you to say.

530
00:41:56,748 --> 00:41:58,872
Maceo, you go with the man here,

531
00:41:59,000 --> 00:42:01,444
he'll show you where
to put these up.

532
00:42:01,586 --> 00:42:04,665
Darling, we've got a lot
of more places to go.

533
00:42:04,835 --> 00:42:06,879
Nice to see you, Luther!

534
00:42:14,850 --> 00:42:17,649
You've got that boy
eating out of your hand!

535
00:42:17,806 --> 00:42:20,570
Luther is the only one
didn't pull my hair,

536
00:42:20,726 --> 00:42:22,695
he sat behind me in Sunday school.

537
00:42:22,817 --> 00:42:27,015
I hope you got a little of that sugar left, cos
we got to spare some on Miss Bertha Mae Spivey.

538
00:42:27,233 --> 00:42:30,254
You gonna ask her to come singI'm gonna ask her for money.

539
00:42:30,421 --> 00:42:33,407
Word is, she got a whole pile
of it squirrelled away.

540
00:42:33,572 --> 00:42:37,575
Daddy... Hey, come on, girl,I got to rest.

541
00:42:40,710 --> 00:42:44,314
Oh, I'm sorry, honey.

542
00:42:44,506 --> 00:42:46,025
You catch your breath, OK.

543
00:42:46,128 --> 00:42:48,332
Yeah.

544
00:42:49,470 --> 00:42:52,833
So why Miss Spivey
gonna give you money,

545
00:42:53,015 --> 00:42:55,574
if you won't let her sing
at the club no more?

546
00:42:55,721 --> 00:42:58,245
I'm gonna make her partner. Partner in what?

547
00:42:58,391 --> 00:42:59,840
The Honeydripper.

548
00:42:59,939 --> 00:43:04,257
But all you ever say, it's just
a hole you pour good money into.

549
00:43:04,480 --> 00:43:07,084
It don't matter.
I'm gonna make her proprietor.

550
00:43:07,233 --> 00:43:10,476
Tress. Like waiter and waitress.

551
00:43:12,201 --> 00:43:14,046
Proprietress.

552
00:43:14,162 --> 00:43:16,361
She got to like the sound of that.

553
00:43:20,460 --> 00:43:23,424
Lovely ladies out to make a purchase.

554
00:43:23,589 --> 00:43:26,548
Is that the same Guitar Sam isThe very one.

555
00:43:26,712 --> 00:43:28,321
What does he look like?

556
00:43:28,427 --> 00:43:33,305
A fine looking man,
a real lady killer from what I hear.

557
00:43:33,552 --> 00:43:35,841
Got that New Orleans style to him.

558
00:43:35,977 --> 00:43:37,461
Well, you ought to have
a picture up there.

559
00:43:37,561 --> 00:43:40,040
We'll be getting some of those
when he come in on the train.

560
00:43:40,184 --> 00:43:44,426
Main thing is,
the man is electrifying

561
00:43:44,646 --> 00:43:46,490
and you know what that means.

562
00:43:46,606 --> 00:43:48,691
OK.

563
00:43:50,867 --> 00:43:55,230
Make like we just come by
to see how how she keeping.

564
00:43:55,455 --> 00:43:59,613
Then I'll kind of mention I'd been
thinking of bringing her on as a partner.

565
00:44:01,920 --> 00:44:03,440
Left the door open.

566
00:44:17,270 --> 00:44:18,310
She gone.

567
00:44:19,230 --> 00:44:23,867
Oh. When she going to be back?

568
00:44:25,820 --> 00:44:27,339
She just gone.

569
00:44:32,785 --> 00:44:34,304
Woke up beside her.

570
00:44:53,099 --> 00:44:54,618
Oh, damn.

571
00:44:54,720 --> 00:44:56,204
24 years.

572
00:44:57,853 --> 00:44:59,937
China doll, go find your mama.

573
00:45:00,063 --> 00:45:01,822
She'll know how to fix up the body.

574
00:45:07,613 --> 00:45:09,772
Laugh and all but...

575
00:45:11,408 --> 00:45:14,167
.. I've been with that woman
24 years.

576
00:45:16,247 --> 00:45:18,286
She gave me the only home
I ever had.

577
00:45:22,546 --> 00:45:23,985
What am I gonna do now?

578
00:45:49,907 --> 00:45:51,946
What's your hurry, boy?

579
00:45:53,744 --> 00:45:55,224
No hurry.

580
00:45:56,331 --> 00:45:58,210
Take your hat off.

581
00:46:00,793 --> 00:46:02,452
Where you headed?

582
00:46:02,561 --> 00:46:04,151
I'm looking for work.

583
00:46:04,256 --> 00:46:06,175
You're not from around here?

584
00:46:06,294 --> 00:46:08,143
No, sir.

585
00:46:08,260 --> 00:46:11,198
Stranger wandering around, no job,

586
00:46:11,361 --> 00:46:14,265
that would make you a vagrant.

587
00:46:14,427 --> 00:46:16,431
But I'm looking.

588
00:46:18,228 --> 00:46:20,627
I got a job for you.
Get in the back.

589
00:46:44,131 --> 00:46:46,135
I can always use another hand.

590
00:46:46,258 --> 00:46:51,215
Well, I caught this young fella in
flagrant violation of the statutes -

591
00:46:51,466 --> 00:46:53,590
gawkery, with intent to mope.

592
00:46:55,266 --> 00:46:56,831
What's he going to run me?

593
00:46:56,935 --> 00:46:59,819
3 a day, plus you feed him lunch.

594
00:46:59,981 --> 00:47:03,579
The sentence, that all depends on how
long you're gonna need the help?

595
00:47:03,771 --> 00:47:05,580
I don't get any trial?

596
00:47:05,694 --> 00:47:09,653
Sure you do, boy, and a speedy
one at that. Meet the judge.

597
00:47:09,861 --> 00:47:11,762
Judge Gatlin.

598
00:47:11,881 --> 00:47:13,748
Grab a sack.

599
00:47:18,249 --> 00:47:21,408
Oh dear, I believe
it's about that time.

600
00:47:24,506 --> 00:47:26,625
Would you care to join me?
No, thank you.

601
00:47:29,386 --> 00:47:31,865
Of course you won't join me,
you don't partake.

602
00:47:32,008 --> 00:47:34,771
That was thoughtless of me.

603
00:47:34,927 --> 00:47:36,892
No, that's all right.

604
00:47:40,105 --> 00:47:46,263
So, you don't take spirits
and what else in your church?

605
00:47:48,030 --> 00:47:52,313
I'm sort of between churchesOh.

606
00:47:52,535 --> 00:47:57,773
I've been thinking about
changing over to the Holiness,

607
00:47:58,036 --> 00:48:00,120
but I haven't been sanctified yet.

608
00:48:00,246 --> 00:48:01,530
Oh.

609
00:48:06,090 --> 00:48:09,648
There's been a minister
in this week.

610
00:48:09,839 --> 00:48:12,363
The tent over by the fairgrounds?

611
00:48:15,350 --> 00:48:18,709
The church I was raised in,
we were Pentecostals.

612
00:48:20,439 --> 00:48:26,277
They wouldn't have anything but
the human voice inside the church.

613
00:48:26,566 --> 00:48:30,289
Dancing, any kind of dancing,

614
00:48:30,486 --> 00:48:32,308
music, card-playing.

615
00:48:32,423 --> 00:48:34,210
It was very strict.

616
00:48:37,332 --> 00:48:39,490
They took up serpents.

617
00:48:39,620 --> 00:48:41,190
I heard of that.

618
00:48:41,294 --> 00:48:45,852
I tell Floyd these stories,
and he's... He's horrified.

619
00:48:47,008 --> 00:48:50,332
They have always been Methodists,
Floyd's family.

620
00:48:50,512 --> 00:48:53,551
It can be a trial, married folks
differ in their religion.

621
00:48:53,719 --> 00:48:56,363
And your husband is a...?

622
00:48:59,479 --> 00:49:01,084
Unaffiliated.

623
00:49:01,190 --> 00:49:03,709
Unaffiliated, I see.

624
00:49:06,279 --> 00:49:09,162
But he has his social club.

625
00:49:09,323 --> 00:49:12,882
The Honeydripper?That is such a colourful name.

626
00:49:13,072 --> 00:49:14,555
Yes.

627
00:49:17,915 --> 00:49:22,673
He must have a great deal
of his energy to it.

628
00:49:22,915 --> 00:49:25,204
It's just him
and Maceo Green runs it,

629
00:49:25,340 --> 00:49:28,783
I go over and cook some
after I get off here.

630
00:49:28,968 --> 00:49:34,326
Well, that's very supportive of you,
considering the sort of environment.

631
00:49:34,594 --> 00:49:38,238
I've been in those bar rooms
most of my life, Miss Amanda.

632
00:49:40,147 --> 00:49:42,426
I see.

633
00:49:49,532 --> 00:49:51,370
I was a singer.

634
00:49:53,119 --> 00:49:56,357
I met Tyrone in the Paradise,
down in Treefork.

635
00:49:56,533 --> 00:49:58,458
China doll was only two.

636
00:50:00,126 --> 00:50:02,850
And I was just...

637
00:50:03,004 --> 00:50:05,882
living alone, you know,

638
00:50:06,043 --> 00:50:08,887
drinking more than I ought,

639
00:50:09,046 --> 00:50:10,731
and then Tyrone...

640
00:50:12,389 --> 00:50:15,553
.. Like a light, come into my life.

641
00:50:15,726 --> 00:50:19,164
People think things
cos he owns the lounge,

642
00:50:19,349 --> 00:50:21,793
but they don't know him.

643
00:50:23,485 --> 00:50:26,363
Small minds are never
in short supply.

644
00:50:28,113 --> 00:50:30,392
People in this town...

645
00:50:36,622 --> 00:50:42,420
I suppose they expected that Floyd,
being from a prominent family,

646
00:50:42,707 --> 00:50:47,510
as prominent as is possible
here in Harmony,

647
00:50:47,754 --> 00:50:51,197
would have chosen somebody more...

648
00:50:56,810 --> 00:50:59,769
In school,
if you didn't have shoes...

649
00:51:06,403 --> 00:51:09,202
Oh, I forgot!

650
00:51:23,379 --> 00:51:26,798
I was going through some of Emily's
old things the other day.

651
00:51:26,982 --> 00:51:30,366
I thought this would look
just darling on your China Doll.

652
00:51:32,181 --> 00:51:35,140
Oh, I don't think that would
near fit her, Miss Amanda.

653
00:51:35,304 --> 00:51:38,067
Why, how old is she, now?

654
00:51:38,223 --> 00:51:40,068
17.

655
00:51:41,189 --> 00:51:42,669
Oh, my...

656
00:51:45,194 --> 00:51:48,512
I must have lost track
somewhere along the line.

657
00:51:48,692 --> 00:51:50,301
17?

658
00:51:50,407 --> 00:51:53,086
It was a very nice thought.

659
00:51:54,829 --> 00:51:57,468
Mama, mama, they need you...

660
00:51:59,793 --> 00:52:00,797
Oh, I'm sorry.

661
00:52:00,876 --> 00:52:05,639
Miss Amanda, I didn't knowChina Doll!

662
00:52:05,882 --> 00:52:09,761
We were just recalling
how you used to play right here,

663
00:52:09,965 --> 00:52:11,289
under this table.

664
00:52:13,432 --> 00:52:16,430
There's not any cash money
that I know of.

665
00:52:16,596 --> 00:52:19,525
She sold a good deal
of the furniture,

666
00:52:19,688 --> 00:52:23,366
but there's still a nice looking
couch in the parlour.

667
00:52:25,110 --> 00:52:28,753
Didn't care about too much,

668
00:52:28,947 --> 00:52:31,286
other than singing
at the Pine Top's place.

669
00:52:31,424 --> 00:52:33,655
You're welcome to look
around the house,

670
00:52:33,788 --> 00:52:35,950
if there's anything
your missus might like.

671
00:52:36,080 --> 00:52:39,159
As long as it's not something
personal to me and Bertha Mae.

672
00:52:39,329 --> 00:52:42,492
It's just...

673
00:52:43,671 --> 00:52:45,310
She's got to go out in style.

674
00:53:32,972 --> 00:53:36,371
You ain't never done this job before?
Can't say I have.

675
00:53:38,102 --> 00:53:43,820
You want to set your pins out wide,
bend over at the hip.

676
00:53:44,104 --> 00:53:47,067
Don't be bobbing up and down
all the time.

677
00:53:47,232 --> 00:53:48,802
When you're up, be up.

678
00:53:48,906 --> 00:53:51,825
When you're on the roll, stay down.

679
00:53:51,988 --> 00:53:55,076
But most important,

680
00:53:55,246 --> 00:53:57,570
you got to get a rhythm.

681
00:53:57,707 --> 00:54:02,665
Everything in life got a rhythm,
even pulling cotton off the plant.

682
00:54:02,915 --> 00:54:06,843
Lay it out for me. Not my rhythm, your rhythm.

683
00:54:07,050 --> 00:54:10,828
That's between you and the day
and the work you got before you.

684
00:54:11,028 --> 00:54:14,771
Once you get it, don't let nothing
or nobody push you off it.

685
00:54:14,969 --> 00:54:17,498
I'm going so slow.

686
00:54:17,644 --> 00:54:20,683
Are you getting paid
by the pound or by the hour?

687
00:54:20,851 --> 00:54:23,552
I ain't getting paid at all,
none of us are.

688
00:54:23,705 --> 00:54:26,337
I suggest you work that
into your rhythm too.

689
00:54:26,487 --> 00:54:29,205
Let's see more picking and
less talking over there.

690
00:54:29,359 --> 00:54:30,924
Getting right to it, boss.

691
00:54:50,803 --> 00:54:52,682
Them boys frying over there.

692
00:54:52,800 --> 00:54:54,609
That's just Gatlin's gang.

693
00:54:54,724 --> 00:54:58,528
He works them people from can
into cane, every damn day.

694
00:54:58,729 --> 00:55:01,407
When the fields get picked,
he bid 'em out to the neighbours.

695
00:55:01,559 --> 00:55:03,249
Harvest time come around here,

696
00:55:03,359 --> 00:55:06,717
you'd better sign with somebody
fast, or get out of sight.

697
00:55:09,114 --> 00:55:10,813
I ate a pick of dust today.

698
00:55:10,923 --> 00:55:12,553
Why don't you get some water?

699
00:55:12,660 --> 00:55:15,304
The only thing that wash out
the dust is whisky.

700
00:55:15,455 --> 00:55:19,733
Ain't enough whisky in this world to
wash out what I swallowed in my life.

701
00:55:19,954 --> 00:55:22,517
What are we playing for?Two bits of ham.

702
00:55:22,664 --> 00:55:24,833
Woo! That's awful steep, ain't it?

703
00:55:24,964 --> 00:55:28,048
Well... I remember playing
this game one night,

704
00:55:28,217 --> 00:55:31,695
Memphis's boss Crumpstown folks
is gambling before they can walk,

705
00:55:31,882 --> 00:55:33,212
caught me a winning streak

706
00:55:33,306 --> 00:55:37,164
that cleaned out half
the sporting men on Beale Street.

707
00:55:37,368 --> 00:55:41,191
I got up from that table,
my money was long as train smoke.

708
00:55:41,392 --> 00:55:42,957
What happened to it?

709
00:55:45,069 --> 00:55:47,588
I spent it all on fine-looking women.

710
00:55:54,453 --> 00:55:58,211
Yo, Mississippi!
His name is Hamilton. Hambo!

711
00:56:00,668 --> 00:56:02,507
You want in on this?

712
00:56:02,623 --> 00:56:04,624
Settle up on pay day.

713
00:56:04,747 --> 00:56:06,714
That your deck of cards?

714
00:56:07,842 --> 00:56:09,486
What if it is?

715
00:56:09,594 --> 00:56:13,197
I'll stay clear of it then.

716
00:56:13,389 --> 00:56:17,508
Are you insinuating? I'm just saying,

717
00:56:30,533 --> 00:56:32,411
Looks like dinner.

718
00:56:32,529 --> 00:56:34,338
A rabbit is a rodent.

719
00:56:34,453 --> 00:56:37,372
A man eat a rabbit,
might as well eat a rat.

720
00:56:37,534 --> 00:56:38,943
Simple country nigger,

721
00:56:39,041 --> 00:56:42,520
afraid to sit down and lose
a little handful of change.

722
00:56:42,707 --> 00:56:44,871
He awful big to mess with.

723
00:56:45,001 --> 00:56:46,930
Don't scare me none.

724
00:56:47,049 --> 00:56:50,807
I'm a stepping razor, man.
I'm trouble on two legs.

725
00:56:53,431 --> 00:56:56,630
Your draw, Junebug. Don't be
dripping no sweat on my cards.

726
00:56:56,805 --> 00:56:59,374
HONKING

727
00:56:59,521 --> 00:57:01,040
Excuse me folks!

728
00:57:04,318 --> 00:57:06,522
Look here!

729
00:57:06,654 --> 00:57:10,771
Y'all heard about the show
we puttin' on at the Honeydripper.

730
00:57:10,985 --> 00:57:13,146
Saturday night.

731
00:57:13,276 --> 00:57:15,403
We got Guitar Sam!

732
00:57:19,542 --> 00:57:22,626
I expect there'll be a nice turnout
for Bertha Mae tomorrow.

733
00:57:22,795 --> 00:57:27,033
Yes, folks who wouldn't have nothing
to do with her when she was alive.

734
00:57:27,253 --> 00:57:29,022
Some of them, maybe.

735
00:57:29,135 --> 00:57:30,854
Still got to pay your respects.

736
00:57:32,847 --> 00:57:36,526
That Slick is gonna have
to find him a new ride.

737
00:57:36,721 --> 00:57:38,250
That's a terrible thing to say.

738
00:57:38,353 --> 00:57:40,277
That's how the man gets over,
is all.

739
00:57:40,397 --> 00:57:45,475
Always sugaring up to some woman
who's got a job or a bankroll.

740
00:57:45,731 --> 00:57:47,136
That's no way to live.

741
00:57:48,780 --> 00:57:50,419
Society is in whirl, baby.

742
00:57:51,533 --> 00:57:55,251
A man's gotta walk through the gates
of hell to get a piece of cheese.

743
00:57:58,123 --> 00:57:59,923
Not so young any more...

744
00:58:01,585 --> 00:58:04,189
.. Lose hold of what little he's got.

745
00:58:04,338 --> 00:58:07,017
If you lose the club,
I'm sure you'll find something else.

746
00:58:07,170 --> 00:58:10,578
In this town, like what?

747
00:58:10,762 --> 00:58:15,000
You know, any time you want,
I could get Miss Amanda to ask...

748
00:58:15,219 --> 00:58:17,021
Watch your feet, Mr Mayor!

