01:20:10,463 --> 01:20:12,273
The guitar ain't been up front,

1002
01:20:12,388 --> 01:20:14,632
since those old pissing
moan blue shouters

1003
01:20:14,765 --> 01:20:17,683
sit their blind asses on the corner
hollering for pennies!

1004
01:20:17,846 --> 01:20:19,376
Old-time music. Daddy?

1005
01:20:19,478 --> 01:20:22,356
Sonny didn't do nothing
to get arrested for.

1006
01:20:22,517 --> 01:20:24,486
He was just looking for work.

1007
01:20:24,608 --> 01:20:28,571
They've hung coloured boys
for less than that, darling.

1008
01:20:28,779 --> 01:20:32,817
Least on the work gang they feed
them, keep their strength up.

1009
01:20:33,028 --> 01:20:35,357
But he doesn't belong there.

1010
01:20:35,494 --> 01:20:39,817
You know, Guitar Sam plays him
an electric.

1011
01:20:40,040 --> 01:20:43,758
But I don't think it's
this no-hole kind of deal.

1012
01:20:43,956 --> 01:20:47,640
Hope he plugs it into
the wrong socket some night

1013
01:20:47,835 --> 01:20:50,559
and electrocutes
his sorry, no-show ass.

1014
01:20:53,180 --> 01:20:54,380
Mace?

1015
01:20:55,808 --> 01:21:03,364
Now, if he showed up here
and our power went out again,

1016
01:21:03,727 --> 01:21:05,256
while he was playing...

1017
01:21:05,358 --> 01:21:07,477
Nah, I fixed it good this time, Ty.

1018
01:21:07,605 --> 01:21:08,895
Eh...

1019
01:21:08,988 --> 01:21:12,426
So he comes out, and he plugs
his axe into the wall...

1020
01:21:12,611 --> 01:21:15,535
He'd come out looking good,
from what I hear!

1021
01:21:15,698 --> 01:21:18,839
All kinds of spangly pants
and jacket!

1022
01:21:19,011 --> 01:21:22,117
Got his name spelt out on the back!

1023
01:21:23,294 --> 01:21:26,133
The clothes, right?!All slick and shiny!

1024
01:21:26,292 --> 01:21:28,336
Flash them gold teeth at them gals!

1025
01:21:28,461 --> 01:21:30,630
Got his sax man behind him.

1026
01:21:30,761 --> 01:21:33,725
Maybe a piano, harmonica and drums.

1027
01:21:33,889 --> 01:21:36,488
Hey, you remember that night
at the Esquire Club,

1028
01:21:36,637 --> 01:21:38,698
when the lights went out in Mobile?

1029
01:21:38,824 --> 01:21:40,815
Yeah, and they took off
with the gate.

1030
01:21:40,937 --> 01:21:43,336
Just stole the damn register
right off the counter!

1031
01:21:43,476 --> 01:21:45,840
They didn't hold Reggie Porter
for it, did they?!

1032
01:21:45,979 --> 01:21:48,903
Nah! They knew it was
this place got robbed!

1033
01:21:49,066 --> 01:21:51,954
Did nobody hold it to Reggie Porter?

1034
01:21:52,115 --> 01:21:55,074
And nobody expected
their money to come back.

1035
01:21:55,239 --> 01:21:58,163
No, cos they was too busy
diving for the pot

1036
01:21:58,326 --> 01:22:00,175
and that trump game got interrupted.

1037
01:22:00,291 --> 01:22:04,849
And nobody suspected that it might
have been Reggie Porter hisself!

1038
01:22:05,083 --> 01:22:08,207
Hisself that pulled the lights!

1039
01:22:10,844 --> 01:22:12,168
No.

1040
01:22:12,262 --> 01:22:13,461
No, Ty. No.

1041
01:22:13,549 --> 01:22:14,678
No. No. No.

1042
01:22:14,764 --> 01:22:18,922
China Doll! You mind the place till
we get back. Hey, come on, Mace.

1043
01:22:19,138 --> 01:22:21,228
Where you going, Daddy?!

1044
01:22:21,355 --> 01:22:25,033
I promised the people Guitar Sam,
and they're going to get Guitar Sam!

1045
01:22:25,228 --> 01:22:27,112
Come on, Mace,
let's get out of here!

1046
01:22:27,230 --> 01:22:28,755
We've got work to do.

1047
01:22:34,660 --> 01:22:37,659
Why are you so interested
in this boy?

1048
01:22:37,825 --> 01:22:39,309
Got a job for him.

1049
01:22:41,042 --> 01:22:44,480
You must be doing pretty well
for yourself out there, Tyrone.

1050
01:22:44,665 --> 01:22:46,629
You're hiring new people on.

1051
01:22:46,751 --> 01:22:49,560
Passing well, yeah.

1052
01:22:49,718 --> 01:22:52,636
But this boy... Name is Sonny.

1053
01:22:52,798 --> 01:22:54,767
Uh-huh.

1054
01:22:54,889 --> 01:22:58,088
Well, he's paying off his debt
to society right now.

1055
01:22:58,263 --> 01:23:00,752
If I was to pull him
out of the field...

1056
01:23:00,896 --> 01:23:04,294
Judge Gatlin paid for your day
of prison labour.

1057
01:23:05,526 --> 01:23:08,884
You willing to pay for him
for the duration of his sentence?

1058
01:23:09,065 --> 01:23:11,709
Which might be?As long as I care to make it.

1059
01:23:14,618 --> 01:23:17,477
Well, I was counting on...

1060
01:23:17,637 --> 01:23:20,988
more of a one-time deal.

1061
01:23:21,170 --> 01:23:24,486
If I can rent him out50.

1062
01:23:26,673 --> 01:23:28,237
It's not just the money.

1063
01:23:28,341 --> 01:23:32,619
There's legalistic principles
involved here. Public safety issues.

1064
01:23:32,840 --> 01:23:35,369
I'll pay you Sunday morning.

1065
01:23:35,515 --> 01:23:38,873
You going to pay me now,
or you can forget about it.

1066
01:23:40,312 --> 01:23:41,871
I don't have it now.

1067
01:23:41,975 --> 01:23:43,379
Hm.

1068
01:23:44,858 --> 01:23:49,416
You think you're too smart for
the rest of us, don't you, Tyrone?

1069
01:23:49,650 --> 01:23:52,174
Think you can go it all by yourself.

1070
01:23:54,744 --> 01:23:56,588
You'd rather eat roofing nails

1071
01:23:56,704 --> 01:23:59,623
than come to me for a favour now,
wouldn't you?

1072
01:23:59,786 --> 01:24:02,070
It's not a favour
if I'm gonna pay for it.

1073
01:24:02,205 --> 01:24:04,248
Oh, you're gonna pay all right.

1074
01:24:05,921 --> 01:24:09,240
If you don't hand over that money
to me by Sunday morning,

1075
01:24:09,420 --> 01:24:11,504
you've got yourself a new partner.

1076
01:24:17,267 --> 01:24:19,066
Same deal as I got with Toussaint.

1077
01:24:19,180 --> 01:24:20,624
What'll that be?

1078
01:24:24,691 --> 01:24:26,330
You'll get the 50.

1079
01:24:27,987 --> 01:24:30,066
And that wife of yours.

1080
01:24:31,156 --> 01:24:33,315
Delilah? Mm-hm.

1081
01:24:34,452 --> 01:24:36,936
Them fried chicken sandwiches.

1082
01:24:37,080 --> 01:24:41,917
If I was to come by now and then
and check in on my interests?

1083
01:24:44,253 --> 01:24:47,017
She be happy to fix you
whatever you want.

1084
01:24:47,173 --> 01:24:51,531
Good. Cos my wife's cooking
would gag a maggot.

1085
01:24:51,756 --> 01:24:56,204
Different people got different kindsYeah.

1086
01:24:56,432 --> 01:24:59,071
Well Lurleen ain't discovered
what hers is yet.

1087
01:24:59,222 --> 01:25:00,546
Let's go fetch that boy.

1088
01:25:17,287 --> 01:25:19,566
Is this the one you want? Mm.

1089
01:25:22,626 --> 01:25:26,545
You got any ideas about running
rabbit on me, best get rid of them now.

1090
01:25:26,751 --> 01:25:28,955
Are you paying my way out?Till Monday.

1091
01:25:29,086 --> 01:25:31,455
How come?

1092
01:25:31,594 --> 01:25:34,033
You like dragging that cotton sack?

1093
01:25:34,175 --> 01:25:37,378
No. Then don't ask questions.

1094
01:25:56,662 --> 01:26:00,145
# Why don't you do right

1095
01:26:00,332 --> 01:26:03,731
# Like some other men do... #

1096
01:26:03,914 --> 01:26:05,803
This size, right?

1097
01:26:05,921 --> 01:26:07,925
But it's got to shine.

1098
01:26:08,048 --> 01:26:10,492
And when you need this? Tonight.

1099
01:26:10,635 --> 01:26:14,718
That's a tall order.
It's got to happen.

1100
01:26:14,931 --> 01:26:21,848
You know, I do my best work,
my fastest work,

1101
01:26:22,183 --> 01:26:24,433
when I'm happy.

1102
01:26:24,567 --> 01:26:28,925
Yeah, I suppose you do.

1103
01:26:30,864 --> 01:26:33,263
You gonna make me happy, baby?

1104
01:26:33,403 --> 01:26:35,327
Uh...

1105
01:26:36,954 --> 01:26:39,917
You come down by the club tonight.

1106
01:26:40,082 --> 01:26:44,260
We having a special show.
Tell 'em at the door, you my guest.

1107
01:26:44,477 --> 01:26:48,621
Food ain't the only thing
a woman needs three times a day.

1108
01:26:52,053 --> 01:26:53,578
What's that, baby?

1109
01:26:53,680 --> 01:26:59,277
Um, that boy gonna need time, try
this jacket on, see how he feels.

1110
01:26:59,555 --> 01:27:00,880
Later, Nadine.

1111
01:27:20,123 --> 01:27:22,807
You got to do something
to the boy's hair, darling.

1112
01:27:22,960 --> 01:27:26,718
They may not know what the real Sam
looked like, but it ain't this.

1113
01:27:26,917 --> 01:27:29,126
I can try.

1114
01:27:29,258 --> 01:27:30,943
What exactly am I supposed to do?

1115
01:27:31,052 --> 01:27:34,210
You're gonna stand up there
with that contraption you got,

1116
01:27:34,383 --> 01:27:36,345
and play Guitar Sam's numbers.

1117
01:27:36,467 --> 01:27:38,359
I can do that with my eyes closed.

1118
01:27:38,477 --> 01:27:41,835
If we can get the audience to
close theirs, we'll be better off.

1119
01:27:42,016 --> 01:27:43,939
Ty! I tracked Mr Trenier down.

1120
01:27:44,982 --> 01:27:47,261
Let's hit it.

1121
01:27:47,396 --> 01:27:49,640
Bye, Daddy.

1122
01:28:06,131 --> 01:28:09,249
You know what you're doing?

1123
01:28:09,420 --> 01:28:12,469
I fix Mama's hair all the time.

1124
01:28:12,637 --> 01:28:15,436
But you ain't been
to that school yet.

1125
01:28:15,594 --> 01:28:18,358
You go to school
to learn your guitar?

1126
01:28:20,062 --> 01:28:21,106
No.

1127
01:28:21,187 --> 01:28:23,625
I might pick up
some things at beauty school,

1128
01:28:23,767 --> 01:28:26,208
but mostly it's for my certificate.

1129
01:28:26,350 --> 01:28:28,553
"And that is a ticket to adventure."

1130
01:28:28,685 --> 01:28:30,819
That's what it says in the brochure.

1131
01:28:30,948 --> 01:28:33,472
People looking for beauty
all over the world.

1132
01:28:33,617 --> 01:28:36,655
You ought to watch out for
them wires sticking down.

1133
01:28:36,823 --> 01:28:38,113
That don't look safe.

1134
01:28:38,205 --> 01:28:40,364
Yeah, power's always going out.

1135
01:28:40,494 --> 01:28:42,618
People getting shocks and whatnot.

1136
01:28:42,747 --> 01:28:45,196
Somebody ought to fix it.

1137
01:28:45,338 --> 01:28:49,296
"Career and beauty
is like money in the bank."

1138
01:28:49,503 --> 01:28:51,644
Says that in the brochure too.

1139
01:28:51,773 --> 01:28:53,845
Plus it isn't physically taxing.

1140
01:28:53,972 --> 01:28:57,890
Yeah, can't see no pretty thing
like you behind a plough.

1141
01:29:01,812 --> 01:29:04,931
I had the rheumatic fever
when I was little.

1142
01:29:05,103 --> 01:29:07,267
It left me with a weak heart.

1143
01:29:07,397 --> 01:29:09,686
Oh.

1144
01:29:09,821 --> 01:29:12,220
Mine been acting kind of funny too.

1145
01:29:12,360 --> 01:29:14,724
About since I laid eyes on you.

1146
01:29:20,583 --> 01:29:24,301
What's that? Just some old
moonshine they keep around.

1147
01:29:24,498 --> 01:29:26,982
What are you gonna do with it?

1148
01:29:28,758 --> 01:29:32,357
They joke about how this stuff
will straighten your hair right out.

1149
01:29:33,763 --> 01:29:36,601
I'll just make yours relax a little.

1150
01:29:52,282 --> 01:29:54,726
Mr Time Trenier.

1151
01:29:54,868 --> 01:29:57,032
Has a name to be reckoned with.

1152
01:29:57,163 --> 01:30:00,441
The story goes you used
to play with Buddy Bolan.

1153
01:30:00,619 --> 01:30:02,589
I played with them all.

1154
01:30:02,710 --> 01:30:07,268
And King Oliver. One band falls
apart, you find yourself another.

1155
01:30:07,502 --> 01:30:10,944
There's never a shortage of bands
down in New Orleans.

1156
01:30:11,129 --> 01:30:13,613
I didn't know
you were giving lessons.

1157
01:30:13,757 --> 01:30:15,521
It pays the rent, almost.

1158
01:30:16,640 --> 01:30:18,884
You interested in a playing job?

1159
01:30:19,018 --> 01:30:22,617
If you can pay, I can play.
You've got to dress sharp.

1160
01:30:24,691 --> 01:30:26,415
It ain't like an all-night thing.

1161
01:30:26,526 --> 01:30:31,484
You just got to start out, and
then there's gonna be an accident.

1162
01:30:31,735 --> 01:30:32,824
An accident?

1163
01:30:32,907 --> 01:30:35,706
Yeah, a sudden loss of power.

1164
01:30:35,864 --> 01:30:37,189
Lights out.

1165
01:30:38,372 --> 01:30:39,972
It's your gig, man.

1166
01:30:40,077 --> 01:30:41,686
8 o'clock.

1167
01:30:41,793 --> 01:30:44,112
This ain't no coloured people's
time.

1168
01:30:44,248 --> 01:30:46,609
And sure ain't New Orleans time.

1169
01:30:46,748 --> 01:30:49,039
I mean, 8 o'clock on the money.

1170
01:30:49,174 --> 01:30:51,533
If you got the green,
I'm on the scene.

1171
01:30:51,672 --> 01:30:53,393
Then that's the deal.

1172
01:30:53,504 --> 01:30:55,156
You know any drummers?

1173
01:30:55,264 --> 01:30:58,823
I bring you one. And nothing fancy.

1174
01:30:59,013 --> 01:31:01,057
Just as long as he keep time.

1175
01:31:01,182 --> 01:31:03,226
Time is my name.

1176
01:31:12,782 --> 01:31:16,880
21, 22, 23, 24, 25, 26, 27, 28.

1177
01:31:17,094 --> 01:31:21,158
Make your mark here, please.

1178
01:31:21,370 --> 01:31:22,734
You owe me 30.

1179
01:31:24,712 --> 01:31:26,596
The book says 28.

1180
01:31:26,714 --> 01:31:31,152
1.50 every 100lb, and I picked...

1181
01:31:31,380 --> 01:31:33,589
2 deducted for stones.

1182
01:31:33,721 --> 01:31:36,645
But I've got no stones in the sack.

1183
01:31:36,808 --> 01:31:40,526
We mill the cotton, son.
There's always stones.

1184
01:31:40,723 --> 01:31:43,527
But there weren't none in my sack.

1185
01:31:45,942 --> 01:31:50,020
We take off 2 a week for stones.
That's the way it's always been.

1186
01:31:53,075 --> 01:31:55,199
Ain't that right, Junebug?

1187
01:31:55,327 --> 01:31:58,126
Yes, sir.
Been that way my whole life.

1188
01:31:59,832 --> 01:32:03,390
You gonna take your pay, son,
or you gonna give it up to charity?

1189
01:32:21,229 --> 01:32:23,028
Wouldn't let nobody mess
with my money like that.

1190
01:32:23,142 --> 01:32:24,991
He took the same 2 off yours.

1191
01:32:25,108 --> 01:32:28,827
Yeah, but you could pave a highway
with the rocks I threw in that mess.

1192
01:32:29,024 --> 01:32:31,925
You country negroes
let the crackers run you like dogs.

1193
01:32:32,087 --> 01:32:34,953
If the sheriff wasn't here
I'd snap your neck, boy.

1194
01:32:35,113 --> 01:32:37,041
Don't let me stop you.

1195
01:32:37,161 --> 01:32:42,559
But first, you're gonna sign
that ledger like you're supposed to.

1196
01:32:42,829 --> 01:32:45,793
Don't want nobody crying
they didn't get their due.

1197
01:32:54,805 --> 01:32:57,644
DELILAH HUMS

1198
01:33:18,497 --> 01:33:21,175
How could you do that?I'm gonna put it back.

1199
01:33:21,327 --> 01:33:23,971
You don't go gambling
with my baby's money.

1200
01:33:24,122 --> 01:33:27,371
I ain't got no man playing.

1201
01:33:27,548 --> 01:33:29,747
I don't care what you took it for.

1202
01:33:29,878 --> 01:33:30,928
I save for China Doll

1203
01:33:31,010 --> 01:33:34,048
and you ain't got not business
putting your fingers on it.

1204
01:33:34,216 --> 01:33:35,786
China don't need any school, baby.

1205
01:33:35,890 --> 01:33:38,649
She could walk into any of those
places right now and get a job.

1206
01:33:38,805 --> 01:33:41,608
There's got to be some line
you won't cross, Ty.

1207
01:33:41,766 --> 01:33:43,668
There's got to be something
you won't do.

1208
01:33:43,786 --> 01:33:45,618
The world start throwing me
a break woman,

1209
01:33:45,734 --> 01:33:47,898
maybe I'll catch religion
and walk the straight and narrow

1210
01:33:48,028 --> 01:33:51,425
like those Bible toppers you
set up with. But until that day...

1211
01:33:51,608 --> 01:33:54,452
Reverend Cutlip was right about you.

1212
01:33:57,495 --> 01:33:59,134
Oh, shit.

1213
01:33:59,242 --> 01:34:00,847
Damn!

1214
01:34:34,784 --> 01:34:36,423
Mr Purvis?

1215
01:34:38,080 --> 01:34:42,998
People call me Ty or they call me
Pine Top, it's Mr Pine Top to you.

1216
01:34:46,338 --> 01:34:49,377
I just want to tell you how
I appreciate the opportunity.

1217
01:34:49,545 --> 01:34:51,029
Right.

1218
01:34:56,307 --> 01:34:59,286
I know every one
of Guitar Sam's songs.

1219
01:34:59,451 --> 01:35:02,395
I know the chords, I know the words.

1220
01:35:06,942 --> 01:35:09,821
China Doll was saying
how you was famous once.

1221
01:35:11,531 --> 01:35:13,055
I was known,

1222
01:35:13,157 --> 01:35:15,037
but never what you call famous.

1223
01:35:18,121 --> 01:35:20,800
How do you get your start?

1224
01:35:24,253 --> 01:35:25,897
Down in Mobile.

1225
01:35:26,004 --> 01:35:29,962
An old professional.

1226
01:35:30,170 --> 01:35:34,059
The name of Joe Dudlow.

1227
01:35:34,263 --> 01:35:36,662
He'd had a stroke on one side.

1228
01:35:38,017 --> 01:35:40,375
Curled him all up.

1229
01:35:42,062 --> 01:35:43,701
Kept on plugging.

1230
01:35:46,525 --> 01:35:51,963
I used to come out and
play his left hand for him.

1231
01:35:52,235 --> 01:35:53,964
This one night,

1232
01:35:54,075 --> 01:35:56,154
he was going hot and heavy.

1233
01:35:58,079 --> 01:35:59,818
His show's just past,

1234
01:35:59,930 --> 01:36:01,600
right at the piano,

1235
01:36:01,708 --> 01:36:04,587
middle of Black Bottom Stomp.

1236
01:36:06,296 --> 01:36:09,535
They'd propped him up at the bar,

1237
01:36:09,712 --> 01:36:11,756
stuck a drink in his hand...

1238
01:36:13,471 --> 01:36:18,628
Told me to keep pounding
those ivories.

1239
01:36:19,852 --> 01:36:24,810
There was a meanness
hanging over them two johns.

1240
01:36:25,061 --> 01:36:28,022
There was murder in the air.

1241
01:36:28,186 --> 01:36:31,077
Stopped playing for the minute,

1242
01:36:31,239 --> 01:36:34,438
come down on you
like a flock of girls.

1243
01:36:34,613 --> 01:36:37,102
Hey.

1244
01:36:37,246 --> 01:36:39,445
This is you.

1245
01:36:41,291 --> 01:36:44,455
